{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Create a government-owned, free software for Making Tax Digital (MTD)",
        "additional_details": "The relationship to HMRC should be secure and simple with no obligatory commercial intermediaries.\r\n\r\nOn commercial platforms we can be beholden to: price increases; reduced functionality in free or non-premium versions; software becoming unavailable through company failure. Yes, free software is available, but it is basic and carries the same risks. \r\n\r\nHMRC must develop a government-owned, free software that cannot fail or be subject to the vicissitudes of the market.",
        "background": "With the roll-out of Making Tax Digital going ahead, HMRC must provide an in-house, government-developed, fully-functional software that allows easy and confident compliance with MTD. Self-employed people should not be obliged to hand data to private companies.",
